Let me re-analyze the mutation more carefully.

The mutation changes `pageurl_path.replace(/\/default\.[a-z]+$/, '/')` to `pageurl_path.replace(/\/default\.[a-z]+$/, "")`.

So for `pageurl_path = "/foo/default.html"`:
- Original: `/foo/default.html` → `/foo/`
- Mutated: `/foo/default.html` → `/foo`

For `pageurl_path = "/default.html"`:
- Original: `/default.html` → `/`
- Mutated: `/default.html` → `` (empty string)

Let me trace through a case where this matters. I need `pageurl_path` to end with `/default.[ext]` and find a link comparison where the trailing slash vs no trailing slash changes the result.

Let me try: page = `http://example.com/default.html`, link = `http://example.com/bar/foo.html`
- `linkurl_path = "/bar/foo.html"`, `linkurl_parts = ["bar", "foo.html"]`
- Original: `pageurl_path = "/"`, `pageurl_parts = []`, diff = 2, returns "internal"
- Mutated: `pageurl_path = ""`, `pageurl_parts = []`, diff = 2, `linkurl_path.includes("")` → true... wait diff=2 not 1, so goes to "internal"

Let me try page = `http://example.com/default.html`, link = `http://example.com/foo.html`:
- `linkurl_path = "/foo.html"`, `linkurl_parts = ["foo.html"]`
- Original: `pageurl_path = "/"`, `pageurl_parts = []`, diff = 1, `"/foo.html".includes("/")` → true → "sublevel"
- Mutated: `pageurl_path = ""`, `pageurl_parts = []`, diff = 1, `"/foo.html".includes("")` → true → "sublevel"

Try page = `http://example.com/foo/default.html`, link = `http://example.com/foo/bar/baz.html`:
- `linkurl_path = "/foo/bar/baz.html"`, `linkurl_parts = ["foo","bar","baz.html"]`
- Original: `pageurl_path = "/foo/"`, `pageurl_parts = ["foo"]`, diff = 2 → "internal"
- Mutated: `pageurl_path = "/foo"`, `pageurl_parts = ["foo"]`, diff = 2 → "internal"

Try page = `http://example.com/foo/default.html`, link = `http://example.com/foo/bar.html`:
- `linkurl_parts = ["foo","bar.html"]`, diff = 1
- Original: `pageurl_path = "/foo/"`, `linkurl_path.includes("/foo/")` → `/foo/bar.html`.includes(`/foo/`) → true → "sublevel"
- Mutated: `pageurl_path = "/foo"`, `linkurl_path.includes("/foo")` → `/foo/bar.html`.includes(`/foo`) → true → "sublevel"

Try page = `http://example.com/foo/default.html`, link = `http://example.com/bar.html`:
- `linkurl_parts = ["bar.html"]`, `pageurl_parts = ["foo"]`, diff = 0
- Original: `pageurl_path = "/foo/"`, `linkurl_without_last_part = ""`, `pageurl_without_last_part = "/foo"` → not equal → "internal"
- Mutated: `pageurl_path = "/foo"`, `linkurl_without_last_part = ""`, `pageurl_without_last_part = ""` → equal → "samelevel"

This is the case! Original returns "internal", mutated returns "samelevel".

